- here's what we're gonna do.
we're gonna get on the elevator

25:03.634 --> 25:06.400
And take it up to 18
and walk down 9 flights.

25:06.400 --> 25:07.467
[elevator dings]

25:07.467 --> 25:08.934
That way everybody's
miserable.

25:15.034 --> 25:17.201
[knock at door]

25:22.567 --> 25:25.134
- [out of breath] mrs. walsh,
sorry to bother you.

25:25.134 --> 25:26.534
Is this a bad time?

25:26.534 --> 25:28.700
- no, it's fine.
i was just working out.

25:28.700 --> 25:29.801
- [laughs]

25:29.801 --> 25:31.168
- we're here
to see your husband.

25:31.168 --> 25:32.500
- come on in.
he's in the kitchen.

25:32.500 --> 25:34.201
I'll go get him.
- thanks.

25:34.201 --> 25:35.801
- are you okay?

25:35.801 --> 25:37.300
- uh, it was
a long walk.

25:37.300 --> 25:38.834
- is the elevator broken?

25:38.834 --> 25:41.834
[all speaking at once]

25:43.767 --> 25:45.600
- i ill don't know
what we're doing here.

25:45.600 --> 25:47.400
We already talked
to this guy.

25:47.400 --> 25:49.268
- we should talk
to him again.

25:49.268 --> 25:50.700
He was there.
he witnessed the accident.

25:50.700 --> 25:51.834
- it wasn't an accident.

25:51.834 --> 25:53.134
- it was an accident.
- here we go.

25:53.134 --> 25:55.333
- mr. monk?

25:55.333 --> 25:57.600
- ah, you remember sharona
and natalie.

25:57.600 --> 25:58.700
I mean, natalie and sharona.

25:58.700 --> 25:59.700
- hi.

25:59.700 --> 26:02.333
- hi. nice surprise.

26:03.667 --> 26:05.500
Can i get you something
to drink?

26:05.500 --> 26:08.001
- uh, no, thank you.
we're fine.

26:08.001 --> 26:11.101
We have a few more questions
about the incident.

26:11.101 --> 26:13.534
We think that mr. fleming

26:13.534 --> 26:15.801
Might have fallen
on purpose.

26:15.801 --> 26:17.634
- really?

26:17.634 --> 26:19.168
- it's just a theory.

26:19.168 --> 26:21.034
- on that morning,

26:21.034 --> 26:25.101
Did you actually see
mr. fleming play any golf?

26:25.101 --> 26:28.201
- well, now that you
mention it,

26:28.201 --> 26:29.600
No, i don't believe i did.

26:29.600 --> 26:30.934
- yeah, but he fell, right?

26:30.934 --> 26:32.801
I mean, he really fell.

26:32.801 --> 26:34.467
He--he didn't pretend.

26:34.467 --> 26:36.300
- well, i was 50 yards away.

26:36.300 --> 26:37.600
It looked real to me.

26:37.600 --> 26:39.567
I don't know
if he's that good of an actor.

26:39.567 --> 26:41.867
- [fake cough]

26:41.867 --> 26:43.700
[cough]

26:43.700 --> 26:45.767
[cough]

26:45.767 --> 26:48.067
On second thought,
i'd love some water.

26:48.067 --> 26:49.567
- sure.

26:49.567 --> 26:51.034
I'll be right back.

26:53.333 --> 26:56.067
- doesn't mean anything.
- don't say that.

26:56.067 --> 26:58.234
- [whispering]
be cool! just--

26:58.234 --> 27:00.268
Just be cool.

27:00.268 --> 27:02.268
- i'm cool.
- no, you're not.

27:02.268 --> 27:03.433
- look at this.

27:09.467 --> 27:11.168
- his wife is reading
these books:

27:11.168 --> 27:13.767
<i>the passions of erica,
it's a series.</i>

27:13.767 --> 27:17.067
See? volume 1, 2, 3, 5,
6, 7, 8, 9, 10.

27:17.067 --> 27:18.134
Where is volume four?

27:18.134 --> 27:19.333
I'll tell you where it is.

27:19.333 --> 27:21.134
It's in your uncle's
apartment.

27:21.134 --> 27:23.300
I saw it lying open
by the couch.

27:23.300 --> 27:25.767
She left it there.

27:27.534 --> 27:29.101
They're having an affair.

27:29.101 --> 27:30.634
- what?
- uncle howie?

27:30.634 --> 27:32.268
- do you think
that he knows?

27:32.268 --> 27:33.767
- he not only knows.

27:33.767 --> 27:35.201
He did something about it.

27:35.201 --> 27:36.667
[dramatic sigh]

27:36.667 --> 27:37.700
He killed your uncle.

27:37.700 --> 27:39.067
- oh! come on!

27:39.067 --> 27:40.400
- think about it.

27:40.400 --> 27:42.667
Howard was sleeping
with carolyn walsh.

27:42.667 --> 27:46.168
What are the odds of her husband
witnessing his fatal accident?

27:46.168 --> 27:48.433
It's off the charts.
it's virtually impossible.

27:48.433 --> 27:50.801
- but they weren't alone.
the caddy was there.

27:50.801 --> 27:52.268
- yeah, the caddy saw
the whole thing.

27:52.268 --> 27:54.700
- that's the beauty of it.
it was a perfect plan.

27:54.700 --> 27:56.867
- i don't understand.

27:56.867 --> 27:58.300
- i'll tell you later.

27:58.300 --> 27:59.300
- no, no, no, no, no.

27:59.300 --> 28:01.333
- you have to tell me now.

28:01.333 --> 28:02.767
Say "here's what happened."

28:02.767 --> 28:04.400
- well, he's right there.

28:04.400 --> 28:06.333
- just tell me.

28:08.834 --> 28:10.867
Say "here's what happened."

28:10.867 --> 28:12.500
- here's what happened.

28:12.500 --> 28:13.934
Walsh knew his wife
was cheating.

28:13.934 --> 28:16.600
He found a letter
or overheard a phone call.

28:16.600 --> 28:19.534
Somehow, he knew,
but he didn't say anything.

28:19.534 --> 28:21.367
He kept it a secret.

28:21.367 --> 28:23.734
He began planning
his revenge.

28:23.734 --> 28:25.567
- we've got orange juice
if you'd like.

28:25.567 --> 28:27.234
- juice is good.
- fresh squeezed would be good.

28:27.234 --> 28:30.333
- [whispers] keep going.
- no! he's right there!

28:30.333 --> 28:33.534
- okay, get over here.

28:33.534 --> 28:35.300
Here, get in here.
just...get in!

28:35.300 --> 28:36.967
- i'm not getting in there!
- get in!

28:36.967 --> 28:39.134
- okay!

28:39.134 --> 28:40.400
- ow!

28:40.400 --> 28:42.101
- okay, keep going.
- we're in a closet!

28:42.101 --> 28:43.600
I can't do this in a closet.

28:43.600 --> 28:45.034
- yes, you can!
just tell me what happened.

28:45.034 --> 28:47.234
Quickly. come on.

28:47.234 --> 28:55.101
[monk talking in indecipherable
fast-forward voice]

28:55.101 --> 28:57.567
And walsh came running up
and killed him--the end.

28:57.567 --> 28:58.934
Can we go now?
- wait--no!

28:58.934 --> 29:01.101
- i don't understand.
- neither do i.

29:01.101 --> 29:02.801
- just do it again.
just slow down.

29:02.801 --> 29:06.234
- oh, my god.

29:06.234 --> 29:08.934
It was walsh's idea.
he came to your uncle.

29:08.934 --> 29:11.500
He said he had a plan
to rip off the country club.

29:11.500 --> 29:13.067
Howard would pretend
to fall down the stairs.

29:13.067 --> 29:15.734
Walsh would be
the unimpeachable witness.

29:15.734 --> 29:17.901
They'd sue the club
and make a fortune.

29:17.901 --> 29:21.067
Walsh must have known
howard was broke.

29:21.067 --> 29:25.934
He knew he'd take the bait.

29:25.934 --> 29:27.467
Okay. where was i?

29:27.467 --> 29:31.201
- he took the bait.

29:31.201 --> 29:33.300
- that morning,
your uncle was on the green.

29:33.300 --> 29:35.500
He was in position.

29:35.500 --> 29:38.101
Meanwhile, walsh made sure
he and the caddy

29:38.101 --> 29:40.268
Were close enough
to see everything.

29:40.268 --> 29:42.734
Your uncle thought
it was just another scam,

29:42.734 --> 29:44.700
But walsh had other ideas.

29:44.700 --> 29:47.001
Can we at least open the door
just a crack?

29:47.001 --> 29:48.201
- [whispers] keep going.

29:48.201 --> 29:49.834
- the caddy ran off
to get help.

29:49.834 --> 29:52.734
That left walsh alone
with your uncle.

29:54.567 --> 29:56.734
It was a perfect plan,
two witnesses.

29:56.734 --> 29:58.967
Walsh himself and his caddy

29:58.967 --> 30:01.801
Had seen your uncle
fall down those stairs.

30:01.801 --> 30:03.567
Nobody would ever suspect
it was murder--the end.

30:03.567 --> 30:04.934
Can we open the door now?

30:04.934 --> 30:07.500
Hey. we were just
taking a little tour.

30:07.500 --> 30:10.067
Is this oak?

30:10.067 --> 30:13.234
- mr. monk, he knows.
that we know.

30:13.234 --> 30:16.534
- i think we're done here.

30:23.433 --> 30:25.268
- [grunts]
hooh!

30:25.268 --> 30:27.300
- are you...okay?

30:27.300 --> 30:29.400
- i'm waiting
for the screaming to stop.

30:29.400 --> 30:32.867
- there's no screaming.
- the screaming inside my head.

30:32.867 --> 30:35.201
You were in a closet
in his house.

30:35.201 --> 30:37.067
He was standing right there.

30:37.067 --> 30:38.801
He obviously heard everything.

30:38.801 --> 30:40.734
Why didn't you just
leave the apartment?

30:40.734 --> 30:42.901
- i tried!
i told them to be cool.

30:42.901 --> 30:44.734
I actually said, "be cool."

30:44.734 --> 30:47.400
- just step outside the house.
talk in the elevator!

30:47.400 --> 30:49.134
- he doesn't take the elevator.
- ha.

30:49.134 --> 30:52.333
- well, we don't have a case
because you tipped him off.

30:52.333 --> 30:54.333
I just got off the phone
with him.

30:54.333 --> 30:56.300
It's a brick wall.
they're all lawyered up.

30:56.300 --> 30:58.934
- what about his wife?
- she's not talking either.

30:58.934 --> 31:00.734
- that's 'cause he probably
threatened her.

31:00.734 --> 31:03.067
- if this is a homicide,
and i believe you're right,

31:03.067 --> 31:05.700
Because you always are,
we're up against it.

31:05.700 --> 31:10.168
We've got nothing!
we have no physical evidence!

31:10.168 --> 31:12.367
- why you looking at me?
it wasn't my fault.

31:14.834 --> 31:16.934
- what does that mean?
- nothing.

31:16.934 --> 31:19.400
- what, are you blaming me now?
- whoa, wait a minute.

31:19.400 --> 31:21.367
It's not her fault.
i mean, her uncle died.

31:21.367 --> 31:22.534
She's got the right to ask
a couple questions.

31:22.534 --> 31:23.934
- randy, you weren't there.

31:23.934 --> 31:25.967
-neither were you.
- no, i wasn't there!

31:25.967 --> 31:28.967
[all shouting, overlapping]

31:35.567 --> 31:38.234
- monk!
monk, what do you think?

31:41.067 --> 31:42.867
Monk!

31:48.168 --> 31:48.968
Taxi!

31:51.269 --> 31:53.869
You on duty?
Yeah.

31:53.870 --> 31:54.870
Thank you.

31:55.667 --> 32:00.567
- where we going?
- i have $52. How far will that take me?

32:00.568 --> 32:01.568
I don't know. Let's find out.

32:05.867 --> 32:07.934
- okay.

32:07.934 --> 32:09.801
Okay, if we hear anything,
we'll let you know.

32:12.234 --> 32:14.268
- is that the captain?
- randy.

32:14.268 --> 32:16.067
- what did he say?

32:16.067 --> 32:17.967
- no news.

32:17.967 --> 32:20.333
- [exhales]
well, he can't go too far.

32:20.333 --> 32:21.767
He can't sleep without
his trudy pillow.

32:21.767 --> 32:23.901
- or that
special red toothbrush.

32:23.901 --> 32:25.634
- or his little flossing kit.

32:25.634 --> 32:27.834
- or the sound machine

32:27.834 --> 32:29.400
With that fog horn noises.

32:29.400 --> 32:31.234
- actually, that one broke.

32:31.234 --> 32:33.634
And they discontinued
the model.

32:33.634 --> 32:35.634
- really?
what did you do?

32:35.634 --> 32:37.801
- i went out and bought
an actual fog horn

32:37.801 --> 32:39.567
And made my own tape.

32:39.567 --> 32:41.467
- [chuckles]

32:41.467 --> 32:44.268
- [laughs]
i'm not kidding.

32:44.268 --> 32:46.934
I have an actual fog horn
sitting in my garage.

32:46.934 --> 32:49.400
- i do not know
how you put up with him.

32:49.400 --> 32:52.667
I don't know
how i put up with him.

32:52.667 --> 32:55.201
Actually, i do.

32:55.201 --> 32:57.600
I loved him.

32:57.600 --> 32:59.600
I swear, this was
the best job i ever had.

32:59.600 --> 33:01.801
Every day was an adventure.

33:01.801 --> 33:03.801
[breathes deeply]

33:03.801 --> 33:07.567
Funny thing is...
adventures are never fun

33:07.567 --> 33:08.901
When you're having 'em,
you know?

33:10.901 --> 33:14.001
- sharona, i'm sorry.

33:14.001 --> 33:16.001
- oh, no.
no, no, no.

33:16.001 --> 33:17.168
I'm the one
who should be sorry.

33:17.168 --> 33:19.534
I was totally out of line.

33:19.534 --> 33:21.367
You're doing
a really good job with him.

33:21.367 --> 33:23.634
Natalie, you're really
patient with him.

33:23.634 --> 33:25.268
It's more than i ever was.

33:25.268 --> 33:28.201
- no, i'm not.
- yeah, you are.

33:28.201 --> 33:29.801
You're a saint.

33:29.801 --> 33:33.201
- sharona, the reason
why i can be nice to mr. monk

33:33.201 --> 33:34.801
And i can be patient
with him

33:34.801 --> 33:36.300
Is because you did
the hard part.

33:36.300 --> 33:37.700
- nah.

33:37.700 --> 33:38.934
- you wereere
right after trudy

33:38.934 --> 33:41.168
When he couldn't even
get out of bed.

33:41.168 --> 33:43.168
- [exhales]
i don't know.

33:43.168 --> 33:44.834
I think i might've been
too tough on him.

33:44.834 --> 33:46.134
- you needed to be tough.

33:46.134 --> 33:49.834
He was in a bad place.

33:49.834 --> 33:53.534
You got him here.

33:53.534 --> 33:55.967
You got him to me.

34:16.168 --> 34:19.367
- mr. monk.

34:19.367 --> 34:20.833
- you found me.

34:20.833 --> 34:23.067
- have you been here all day?

34:23.067 --> 34:25.699
- i've been here
for 12 years.

34:25.699 --> 34:27.034
- mr. monk, you can
come home now.

34:27.034 --> 34:29.867
We're fine.
- unh.

34:29.867 --> 34:31.034
- hey, i know
you saw us fighting,

34:31.034 --> 34:33.001
I know you got scared,

34:33.001 --> 34:34.367
And we're really
sorry about it.

34:34.367 --> 34:36.134
- yeah, but we talked
about it,

34:36.134 --> 34:39.201
And we decided we really
have to nail this guy walsh.

34:39.201 --> 34:41.168
- absolutely.
i don't care about the lawsuit.

34:41.168 --> 34:43.067
I don't care about that money.
you were right.

34:43.067 --> 34:44.934
Howie fleming was my uncle.

34:44.934 --> 34:46.534
He wasn't perfect,
but he was family,

34:46.534 --> 34:47.934
And we can't let walsh
get away with it.

34:47.934 --> 34:49.801
- so we want to go back
to the country club.

34:49.801 --> 34:51.867
- mm-hmm, i mean, maybe we
overlooked a clue or something.

34:51.867 --> 34:53.567
- what kind of clue?

34:53.567 --> 34:55.168
- we don't know.
that's where you come in.

34:55.168 --> 34:56.734
Come on.
- come on.

34:56.734 --> 35:00.400
Let's go home.
we'll make you dinner.

35:00.400 --> 35:03.168
Is tuesday still
chicken pot pie?

35:03.168 --> 35:04.801
- why, what have you heard?

35:04.801 --> 35:08.001
- of course it is.
i don't even know why i asked.

35:12.433 --> 35:14.667
[sharona grunts]

35:14.667 --> 35:18.201
Even a cancelled card can
come in handy sometimes.

35:18.201 --> 35:19.367
Where do we start?

35:19.367 --> 35:22.201
- where do we start?
right here.

35:25.467 --> 35:27.767
This one's locked.
- wait, hold on.

35:32.234 --> 35:34.101
- where'd you learn that?
- self-taught.

35:38.934 --> 35:42.034
- fujikawa.

35:44.634 --> 35:46.067
- the battery was dead.
piece of crap phone.

35:46.067 --> 35:48.234
Thanks for nothing,
fujikawa cellular.

35:48.234 --> 35:51.134
- it's from the caddy's
cell phone.

35:51.134 --> 35:55.801
Walsh must've
switched batteries.

35:55.801 --> 35:59.467
That morning, walsh put a new
battery in the caddy's phone.

35:59.467 --> 36:02.500
One that wasn't
charged yet.

36:02.500 --> 36:05.634
He had to be sure the caddy
couldn't call for help.

36:05.634 --> 36:06.634
- is that it?
is that proof?

36:06.634 --> 36:08.201
- no.

36:08.201 --> 36:12.067
He could explain this.
but maybe--

36:12.067 --> 36:14.667
- what?
- the caddy's cell phone.

36:14.667 --> 36:17.201
If the new battery
is still inside it,

36:17.201 --> 36:19.567
It would have walsh's
fingerprints all over it.

36:19.567 --> 36:20.901
He'd have a hard time
explaining that.

36:20.901 --> 36:22.734
- my god, we have to find
that caddy.

36:22.734 --> 36:24.168
- hey, mr. walsh,
how you doing?

36:24.168 --> 36:25.700
- oh, my god.
- walsh.

36:25.700 --> 36:29.001
- forget the caddy.
we gotta stop him!

36:47.367 --> 36:49.500
- number three.

36:49.500 --> 36:52.967
And...nice putt!
excellent.

36:52.967 --> 36:54.600
- let's go to 14.

37:00.734 --> 37:04.333
- it's all over walsh.

37:04.333 --> 37:06.534
Oh, god.

37:06.534 --> 37:08.867
Unh! oh!

37:11.168 --> 37:14.234
- mr. monk, are you okay?

37:14.234 --> 37:16.268
- let him go.
just let him go.

37:16.268 --> 37:18.034
He wins.
it's over, it's over.

37:18.035 --> 37:19.035
We're not letting him go.

37:24.067 --> 37:26.667
- jerry! your cell phone!

37:26.667 --> 37:27.967
I need your phone!

37:27.967 --> 37:29.333
- faster!

37:37.767 --> 37:40.734
[sharona and walsh grunting]

37:57.234 --> 38:01.134
- oh!

38:01.134 --> 38:02.534
- okay.

38:02.534 --> 38:05.901
Okay. we got him.
we did it.

38:05.901 --> 38:07.467
I was back there...

38:07.467 --> 38:08.801
I was making sure
he didn't double back.

38:08.801 --> 38:10.101
What do you say?

38:10.101 --> 38:11.634
Are we gonna talk
to this caddy?

38:11.634 --> 38:15.367
Come on, let's not...
dillydally.

38:15.367 --> 38:18.700
Let's go.

38:18.700 --> 38:20.600
Let's go!

38:22.734 --> 38:25.634
- sit down. beautiful.

38:25.634 --> 38:27.168
- mr. hanks.

38:27.168 --> 38:28.934
- yeah, we need your phone.
- my phone?

38:28.934 --> 38:31.400
- yeah, the police are gonna
keep it for a while.

38:31.400 --> 38:33.134
- what do you mean they're
gonna keep it for a while?

38:33.134 --> 38:35.067
- it's a long story.
- don't worry.

38:35.067 --> 38:37.433
The city of san francisco will
provide you with an upgrade.

38:37.433 --> 38:40.467
- adrian.

38:40.467 --> 38:42.534
You were right.

38:42.534 --> 38:43.934
He's my uncle.

38:43.934 --> 38:45.567
I know i only...
met him twice,

38:45.567 --> 38:47.433
But twice is enough.

38:47.433 --> 38:51.001
I guess i never--ow!

38:51.001 --> 38:52.834
- sharona!
- are you okay?

38:52.834 --> 38:54.467
- oh, god,
i think i broke my arm.

38:54.467 --> 38:55.934
- oh, my god.

38:55.934 --> 38:57.234
I can't believe they never
fixed that step.

38:59.235 --> 39:00.635
This is my lucky day.

39:01.333 --> 39:04.168
- benjy's going to college.

39:04.168 --> 39:05.667
Ow!

39:15.233 --> 39:16.767
- you sure you don't need
a ride?

39:16.767 --> 39:18.801
- oh, no, no, no, my friend
is picking me up.

39:18.801 --> 39:21.901
- oh, sharona,
it was great to see you.

39:21.901 --> 39:24.300
- you too, boss.

39:24.300 --> 39:26.434
You know, i have to say
i'm gonna sleep

39:26.434 --> 39:29.167
A lot better now i--

39:29.167 --> 39:31.467
